@osiris9128 You're making a mistake I used to make as well. Being leftwing or rightwing doesn't have to mean that you're picking a team who you have to agree with no matter what. It just describes what positions you support politically, and whether or not those positions were arrived at rationally is a separate matter.
Or in other words, having some leftwing views and some rightwing views doesn't mean that you have more common sense than those who have exclusively leftwing or rightwing views.
Or in other other words, you can arrive at a strongly polarised political viewpoint through rational and logical thought.

